4152505Di2015UniqueSeparatorstep = 60Â°
4152505Di2015UniqueSeparatorpublic static Point[] CalculateVertices(int nSides, int nSideLength, Point ptFirstVertex)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    if (nSides < 3)Di2015NewLine        throw new ArgumentException("Polygons can't have less than 3 sides...");Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    var aptsVertices = new Point[nSides];Di2015NewLine    var deg = (180.0 * (nSides - 2)) / nSides;Di2015NewLine    var step = 360.0 / nSides;Di2015NewLine    var rad = deg * (Math.PI / 180);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    double nSinDeg = Math.Sin(rad);Di2015NewLine    double nCosDeg = Math.Cos(rad);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    aptsVertices[0] = ptFirstVertex;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    for (int i = 1; i < aptsVertices.Length; i++)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        double x = aptsVertices[i - 1].X - nCosDeg * nSideLength;Di2015NewLine        double y = aptsVertices[i - 1].Y - nSinDeg * nSideLength;Di2015NewLine        aptsVertices[i] = new Point((int)x, (int)y);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        //recalculate the degree for the next vertexDi2015NewLine        deg -= step;Di2015NewLine        rad = deg * (Math.PI / 180);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        nSinDeg = Math.Sin(rad);Di2015NewLine        nCosDeg = Math.Cos(rad);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine    return aptsVertices;Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

4154932Di2015UniqueSeparator private static int SendVarData(Socket s, byte[] data)Di2015NewLine {Di2015NewLine            int total = 0;Di2015NewLine            int size = data.Length;Di2015NewLine            int dataleft = size;Di2015NewLine            int sent;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            byte[] datasize = new byte[4];Di2015NewLine            datasize = BitConverter.GetBytes(size);Di2015NewLine            sent = s.Send(datasize);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            while (total < size)Di2015NewLine            {Di2015NewLine                sent = s.Send(data, total, dataleft, SocketFlags.None);Di2015NewLine                total += sent;Di2015NewLine                dataleft -= sent;Di2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLine            return total;Di2015NewLine }Di2015NewLine

4159570Di2015UniqueSeparator// The custom data structure, deserialized from JSON.Di2015NewLineCustomData data = ...;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine// The type of Employee.Di2015NewLineType type = typeof(Employee);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine// Create a map of the property info to the ordinal in theDi2015NewLine// Columns.Di2015NewLineIDictionary<int, PropertyInfo> propertyMap = data.Columns.Di2015NewLine    Select((p, i) => Di2015NewLine        new { Index = i, PropertyInfo = type.GetProperty(p) }).Di2015NewLine    ToDictionary(p => p.Index, p => p.PropertyInfo);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine// Cycle through the rows in the data.Di2015NewLinevar query =Di2015NewLine    // Cycle through all of the rows.Di2015NewLine    from row in Enumerable.Range(0, data.Data.GetLength(0))Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    // Create the instance.Di2015NewLine    let instance = new Employee()Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    // For each column in the row.Di2015NewLine    from column in Enumerable.Range(0, data.Data.GetLength(1))Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    // Lookup the property info.Di2015NewLine    let propertyInfo = propertyMap[column]Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    // Select the instance, the property, and the value.Di2015NewLine    select { Di2015NewLine        // This is used for grouping purposes, sinceDi2015NewLine        // you can't guarantee that the type you are serializingDi2015NewLine        // to will have natural identity properties andDi2015NewLine        // you know the row corresponds to one singular instance.Di2015NewLine        Row = row,Di2015NewLine        Instance = instance, Di2015NewLine        PropertyInfo = propertyInfo,Di2015NewLine        Value = data.Data[row, column]Di2015NewLine    };Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine// Iterate through the items, setting the instance values.Di2015NewLineforeach (var propertyAndData in query)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    // Set the property value on the instance.Di2015NewLine    propertyAndData.PropertyInfo.Di2015NewLine        SetValue(propertyAndData.Instance, Value, null);Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine// Group by the row and get the first item in each sequence.Di2015NewLineIEnumerable<Employee> employees =Di2015NewLine    from item in queryDi2015NewLine    groupby item by item.Row into gDi2015NewLine    select g.First();Di2015NewLine

4160022Di2015UniqueSeparatorint[] myArray = {1,2,3};Di2015NewLinePassByVal(myArray);Di2015NewLinePassByRef(ref myArray);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLinePassByVal(int[] array){Di2015NewLine    // the function copy the value of the pointer in a new location of memoryDi2015NewLine    // the "copied" pointer stil poin to the array 123    Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    // now you are modifying the object pointed by THE COPY of the pointerDi2015NewLine    // the original pointer stil point to array 123Di2015NewLine    // the copoy of the pointer will point to array 456Di2015NewLine    array = new int[] {7,8,9}; Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine} // will not workDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLinePassByRef(ref int[] array){Di2015NewLine   // here you are passing the pointer without creating a copy of it in a Di2015NewLine   // new location of memoryDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine   // we have not a original pointer and a "copyed" pointerDi2015NewLine   // we have only the original pointer and now whe point it to array 10,11,12Di2015NewLine   array = new int[] {10,11,12}; Di2015NewLine}  // will workDi2015NewLine

4166878Di2015UniqueSeparatorprivate Regex captures = new Regex(@"\\(.+?\\)");Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLinepublic string ConstructFolderName(string firstGroup, string secondGroup, string pattern)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    MatchCollection matches = captures.Matches(pattern);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    Regex firstCapture = new Regex(matches[0].Value);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    if (!firstCapture.IsMatch(firstGroup))Di2015NewLine        throw new FormatException("firstGroup");Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    Regex secondCapture = new Regex(matches[1].Value);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    if (!secondCapture.IsMatch(secondGroup))Di2015NewLine        throw new FormatException("secondGroup");Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    return pattern.Replace(firstCapture.ToString(), firstGroup).Replace(secondCapture.ToString(), secondGroup);Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

4167772Di2015UniqueSeparatorprivate Geocoordinate MidPoint(Geocoordinate posA, Geocoordinate posB)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine   Geocoordinate midPoint = new Geocoordinate();Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine   double dLon = DegreesToRadians(posB.Longitude - posA.Longitude);Di2015NewLine   double Bx = Math.Cos(DegreesToRadians(posB.Latitude)) * Math.Cos(dLon);Di2015NewLine   double By = Math.Cos(DegreesToRadians(posB.Latitude)) * Math.Sin(dLon);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine   midPoint.Latitude = RadiansToDegrees(Math.Atan2(Di2015NewLine                Math.Sin(DegreesToRadians(posA.Latitude)) + Math.Sin(DegreesToRadians(posB.Latitude)),Di2015NewLine                Math.Sqrt(Di2015NewLine                    (Math.Cos(DegreesToRadians(posA.Latitude)) + Bx) *Di2015NewLine                    (Math.Cos(DegreesToRadians(posA.Latitude)) + Bx) + By * By))); Di2015NewLine                 // (Math.Cos(DegreesToRadians(posA.Latitude))) + Bx) + By * By)); // Your CodeDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine   midPoint.Longitude = posA.Longitude + RadiansToDegrees(Math.Atan2(By, Math.Cos(DegreesToRadians(posA.Latitude)) + Bx));Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine   return midPoint;Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

Value { get; private set; }Di2015NewLine        public Node Parent { get; private set; }Di2015NewLine        public List<Node> Children { get; private set; }Di2015NewLine        public Node(char? c, Node parent)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            this.Value = c;Di2015NewLine            this.Parent = parent;Di2015NewLine            this.Children = new List<Node>();Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    public static string GetRegex(IEnumerable<string> tokens)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        var root = new Node(null,null);Di2015NewLine        foreach (var token in tokens)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            var current = root;Di2015NewLine            for (int i = 0; i < token.Length; i++)Di2015NewLine            {Di2015NewLine                char c = token[i];Di2015NewLine                var node = current.Children.FirstOrDefault(x => x.Value.Value == c);Di2015NewLine                if (node == null)Di2015NewLine                {Di2015NewLine                    node = new Node(c,current);Di2015NewLine                    current.Children.Add(node);Di2015NewLine                }Di2015NewLine                current = node;Di2015NewLine            }   Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine        return BuildRexp(root);Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    private static string BuildRexp(Node root)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        string s = "";Di2015NewLine        bool addBracket = root.Children.Count > 1;Di2015NewLine        // uncomment the following line to avoid first brakets wrapping (occurring in case of multiple root's children)Di2015NewLine        // addBracket = addBracket && (root.Parent != null); Di2015NewLine        if (addBracket)Di2015NewLine            s += "(";Di2015NewLine        for(int i = 0; i < root.Children.Count; i++)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            var child = root.Children[i];Di2015NewLine            s += child.Value;Di2015NewLine            s += BuildRexp(child);Di2015NewLine            if (i < root.Children.Count - 1)Di2015NewLine                s += "|";Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine        if (addBracket)Di2015NewLine            s += ")";Di2015NewLine        return s;Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

4190320Di2015UniqueSeparatorfunction distanceFromTo($latitude1,$longitude1,$latitude2,$longitude2,$km){Di2015NewLine  $latitude1  = deg2rad($latitude1);Di2015NewLine  $longitude1 = deg2rad($longitude1);Di2015NewLine  $latitude2  = deg2rad($latitude2);Di2015NewLine  $longitude2 = deg2rad($longitude2);Di2015NewLine  $delta_latitude  = $latitude2  - $latitude1;Di2015NewLine  $delta_longitude = $longitude2 - $longitude1;Di2015NewLine  $temp = pow(sin($delta_latitude/2.0),2) + cos($latitude1) * cos($latitude2) * pow(sin($delta_longitude/2.0),2);Di2015NewLine  $earth_radius = 3956;Di2015NewLine  $distance = $earth_radius * 2 * atan2(sqrt($temp),sqrt(1-$temp));Di2015NewLine  if ($km)Di2015NewLine    $distance = $distance * 1.609344;Di2015NewLine  return $distance;Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

4193308Di2015UniqueSeparatorThe runtime uses the following steps to resolve an assembly reference:Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLineDetermines the correct assembly version by examining applicable configuration files,    Di2015NewLineincluding the application configuration file, publisher policy file, and machine  Di2015NewLineconfiguration file. Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLineIf the configuration file is located on a remote machine, the    Di2015NewLineruntime must locate and download the application configuration file first.Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLineChecks whether the assembly name has been bound to before and, if so, uses the Di2015NewLinepreviously loaded assembly.Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLineChecks the global assembly cache. If the assembly is found there, the runtime uses this  Di2015NewLineassembly.Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLineProbes for the assembly using the following steps:Di2015NewLineIf configuration and publisher policy do not affect the original reference and if the Di2015NewLinebind request was created using the Assembly.LoadFrom method, the runtime checks for Di2015NewLinelocation hints.Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLineIf a codebase is found in the configuration files, the runtime checks only this Di2015NewLinelocation. If this probe fails, the runtime determines that the binding request failed  Di2015NewLineand no other probing occurs.Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLineProbes for the assembly using the heuristics described in the probing section. If the   Di2015NewLineassembly is not found after probing, the runtime requests the Windows Installer to Di2015NewLineprovide the assembly. This acts as an install-on-demand feature.Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLineNote:   There is no version checking for assemblies without strong names, nor does the Di2015NewLineruntime check in the global assembly cache for assemblies without strong names.Di2015NewLine

4194158Di2015UniqueSeparatorprivate void dataGrid_SizeChanged(object sender, EventArgs e)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    ResizeGridColumns();Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLineprivate void ResizeGridColumns()Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    //get sum of non-resizable columns widthDi2015NewLine    int diffWidth = 0;Di2015NewLine    foreach (DataGridViewColumn col in this.dataGrid.Columns)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        if (col.Resizable == DataGridViewTriState.False && col.Visible) diffWidth += col.Width;Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    //calculate available widthDi2015NewLine    int totalResizableWith = this.dataGrid.Width - diffWidth;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    //resize column width based on previous proportionsDi2015NewLine    this.dataGrid.ColumnWidthChanged -= new DataGridViewColumnEventHandler(dataGrid_ColumnWidthChanged);Di2015NewLine    for (int i = 0; i < this.colWidthRaport.Count; i++)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        tryDi2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            if (this.dataGrid.Columns[i].Resizable != DataGridViewTriState.False && this.dataGrid.Columns[i].Visible)Di2015NewLine            {Di2015NewLine                this.dataGrid.Columns[i].Width = (int)Math.Floor((decimal)totalResizableWith / this.colWidthRaport[i]);Di2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine        catch { }Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine    this.dataGrid.ColumnWidthChanged += new DataGridViewColumnEventHandler(dataGrid_ColumnWidthChanged);Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLineprivate void dataGrid_ColumnWidthChanged(object sender, DataGridViewColumnEventArgs e)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    CalculateGridColWidthsRaport();Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine/// <summary>Calculates the proportions between grid width and column width</summary>Di2015NewLineprivate void CalculateGridColWidthsRaport()Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    //get sum of non-resizable columns widthDi2015NewLine    int diffWidth = 0;Di2015NewLine    int colWidthsSum = 0;Di2015NewLine    foreach (DataGridViewColumn col in this.dataGrid.Columns)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        if (col.Visible)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            colWidthsSum += col.Width;Di2015NewLine            if (col.Resizable == DataGridViewTriState.False) diffWidth += col.Width;Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine    colWidthsSum += 24;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    //calculate available withDi2015NewLine    int totalResizableWith = colWidthsSum - diffWidth;// this.dataGrid.Width - diffWidth;Di2015NewLine    if (this.ParentForm.WindowState == FormWindowState.Maximized)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        totalResizableWith = this.dataGrid.Width - diffWidth;Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    //calculate proportions of each column relative to the available widthDi2015NewLine    this.colWidthRaport = new List<decimal>();Di2015NewLine    foreach (DataGridViewColumn col in this.dataGrid.Columns)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        this.colWidthRaport.Add((decimal)totalResizableWith / (decimal)col.Width);Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

((uint)(joinParams.Properties["ReturnValue"].Value) != 0)Di2015NewLine      {Di2015NewLine        // Join to domain didn't workDi2015NewLine        _lh.Log(LogHandler.LogType.Fatal, 4204198Di2015UniqueSeparator// Returns last index of the value that is the minimum.Di2015NewLinepublic static int IndexOfMin(this IEnumerable<int> source)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine   if(source == null)Di2015NewLine     throw new ArgumentNullException("source");Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine   int minValue = int.MaxValue;Di2015NewLine   int minIndex = -1;Di2015NewLine   int index = -1;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine   foreach(int num in source)Di2015NewLine   {Di2015NewLine      index++;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine      if(num <= minValue)Di2015NewLine      {Di2015NewLine         minValue = num;Di2015NewLine         minIndex = index;Di2015NewLine      }Di2015NewLine   }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine   if(index == -1)Di2015NewLine     throw new InvalidOperationException("Sequence was empty");Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine   return minIndex;Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

WindingDirectionDi2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    Clockwise,Di2015NewLine    CounterClockWiseDi2015NewLine}Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLinepublic static WindingDirection DetermineWindingDirection(PointF[] polygon)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    // find a point in the middleDi2015NewLine    float middleX = polygon.Average(p => p.X);Di2015NewLine    float middleY = polygon.Average(p => p.Y);Di2015NewLine    var pointInPolygon = new PointF(middleX, middleY);Di2015NewLine    Console.WriteLine("MiddlePoint = {0}", pointInPolygon);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    double w = 0;Di2015NewLine    var points = polygon.Select(point =>Di2015NewLine                                    { Di2015NewLine                                        var newPoint = new PointF(point.X - pointInPolygon.X, point.Y - pointInPolygon.Y);Di2015NewLine                                        Console.WriteLine("New Point: {0}", newPoint);Di2015NewLine                                        return newPoint;Di2015NewLine                                    }).ToList();Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    for (int i = 0; i < points.Count; i++)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        var secondPoint = i + 1 == points.Count ? 0 : i + 1;Di2015NewLine        double X = points[i].X;Di2015NewLine        double Xp1 = points[secondPoint].X;Di2015NewLine        double Y = points[i].Y;Di2015NewLine        double Yp1 = points[secondPoint].Y;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        if (Y * Yp1 < 0)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            double r = X + ((Y * (Xp1 - X)) / (Y - Yp1));Di2015NewLine            if (r > 0)Di2015NewLine                if (Y < 0)Di2015NewLine                    w = w + 1;Di2015NewLine                elseDi2015NewLine                    w = w - 1;Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine .5;Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine        else if ((Yp1 == 0) && (Xp1 > 0))Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            if (Y < 0)Di2015NewLine                w = w + .5;Di2015NewLine            elseDi2015NewLine                w = w - .5;Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine    return w > 0 ? 4219352Di2015UniqueSeparator    public static void DrawDashedLine(this Graphics g, Pen p, float dash, float gap, PointF s, PointF e)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine      float dx = e.X - s.X;Di2015NewLine      float dy = e.Y - s.Y;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine      float len = (float)Math.Sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy);Di2015NewLine      float remainder = len;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine      float vx = dx / len;Di2015NewLine      float vy = dy / len;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine      if (len <= dash + gap)Di2015NewLine      {Di2015NewLine        g.DrawLine(p, s, e);Di2015NewLine        return;Di2015NewLine      }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine      PointF last = s;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine      while (remainder > dash + gap)Di2015NewLine      {Di2015NewLine        PointF p1 = new PointF(last.X, last.Y);Di2015NewLine        PointF p2 = new PointF(p1.X + vx*dash, p1.Y + vy*dash);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        g.DrawLine(p, p1, p2);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        last = new PointF(p2.X + vx*gap, p2.X + vy*gap);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        remainder = remainder - dash - gap;Di2015NewLine      }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine      if (remainder > 0)Di2015NewLine      {Di2015NewLine        g.DrawLine(p, last, e);Di2015NewLine      }Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine  }Di2015NewLine

4219369Di2015UniqueSeparatorprotected override Size ArrangeOverride(Size finalSize)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            // desiredWidth and desiredHeight are the width and height of the element that's being adorned.  Di2015NewLine            // These will be used to place the ResizingAdorner at the corners of the adorned element.  Di2015NewLine            double desiredWidth = AdornedElement.DesiredSize.Width;Di2015NewLine            double desiredHeight = AdornedElement.DesiredSize.Height;Di2015NewLine            // adornerWidth & adornerHeight are used for placement as well.Di2015NewLine            double adornerWidth = this.DesiredSize.Width;Di2015NewLine            double adornerHeight = this.DesiredSize.Height;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            topLeft.Arrange(new Rect(-adornerWidth / 2, -adornerHeight / 2, adornerWidth, adornerHeight));Di2015NewLine            topRight.Arrange(new Rect(desiredWidth - adornerWidth / 2, -adornerHeight / 2, adornerWidth, adornerHeight));Di2015NewLine            bottomLeft.Arrange(new Rect(-adornerWidth / 2, desiredHeight - adornerHeight / 2, adornerWidth, adornerHeight));Di2015NewLine            bottomRight.Arrange(new Rect(desiredWidth - adornerWidth / 2, desiredHeight - adornerHeight / 2, adornerWidth, adornerHeight));Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            // Return the final size.Di2015NewLine            return finalSize;Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine

4221864Di2015UniqueSeparatorpublic static byte[] Generate()Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine  var templatePath = HttpContext.Current.Server.MapPath("~/my_template.pdf");Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine  // Based on:Di2015NewLine  // http://www.johnnycode.com/blog/2010/03/05/using-a-template-to-programmatically-create-pdfs-with-c-and-itextsharp/Di2015NewLine  var reader = new PdfReader(templatePath);Di2015NewLine  var outStream = new MemoryStream();Di2015NewLine  var stamper = new PdfStamper(reader, outStream);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine  var form = stamper.AcroFields;Di2015NewLine  var fieldKeys = form.Fields.Keys;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine  foreach (string fieldKey in fieldKeys)Di2015NewLine  {Di2015NewLine    if (form.GetField(fieldKey) == "MyTemplatesOriginalTextFieldA")Di2015NewLine      form.SetField(fieldKey, "1234");Di2015NewLine    if (form.GetField(fieldKey) == "MyTemplatesOriginalTextFieldB")Di2015NewLine      form.SetField(fieldKey, "5678");Di2015NewLine  }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine  // "Flatten" the form so it wont be editable/usable anymore  Di2015NewLine  stamper.FormFlattening = true;  Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine  stamper.Close();Di2015NewLine  reader.Close();Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine  return outStream.ToArray();Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

4241284Di2015UniqueSeparator// Use standard ChildDi2015NewLinepublic Child Add(string initInfo)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    Child newChild = new Child(this.Parent);Di2015NewLine    // There's actually a bit more coding before Initialize()Di2015NewLine    // in the real thing, but nothing relevant to the example.Di2015NewLine    newChild.Initialize(initInfo);Di2015NewLine    List.Add(newChild);Di2015NewLine    return newChild;Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine// Overload for derived Child.Di2015NewLinepublic Child Add(Type childDerivative, string initInfo)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    if (!childDerivative.IsSubclassOf(typeof(Child)))Di2015NewLine        throw new ArgumentException("Not a subclass of Child.");Di2015NewLine    ConstructorInfo ci = childDerivative.GetConstructor(Di2015NewLine        BindingFlags.Instance |Di2015NewLine        BindingFlags.Public | BindingFlags.NonPublic |Di2015NewLine        BindingFlags.FlattenHierarchy |Di2015NewLine        BindingFlags.ExactBinding, Di2015NewLine        null, new Type[] { typeof(Parent) }, null);Di2015NewLine    if (ci == null)Di2015NewLine        throw new InvalidOperationException("Failed to find proper constructor.");Di2015NewLine    newChild = (Child)ci.Invoke(new Object[] { this.Parent });Di2015NewLine    newChild.Initialize(initInfo);Di2015NewLine    List.Add(newChild);Di2015NewLine    return newChild;Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

4243079Di2015UniqueSeparator        public static bool IsInPolygon(Point[] poly, Point point)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine           var coef = poly.Skip(1).Select((p, i) => Di2015NewLine                                           (point.Y - poly[i].Y)*(p.X - poly[i].X) Di2015NewLine                                         - (point.X - poly[i].X) * (p.Y - poly[i].Y))Di2015NewLine                                   .ToList();Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            if (coef.Any(p => p == 0))Di2015NewLine                return true;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            for (int i = 1; i < coef.Count(); i++)Di2015NewLine            {Di2015NewLine                if (coef[i] * coef[i - 1] < 0)Di2015NewLine                    return false;Di2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLine            return true;Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine

4249412Di2015UniqueSeparatorSystem.DirectoryServices

4249412Di2015UniqueSeparatorprivate IEnumerable<DirectoryEntry> GetDomains() {Di2015NewLine    ICollection<string> domains = new List<string>();Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    // Querying the current Forest for the domains within.Di2015NewLine    foreach(Domain d in Forest.GetCurrentForest().Domains)Di2015NewLine        domains.Add(d.Name);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    return domains;Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLineprivate string GetDomainFullName(string friendlyName) {Di2015NewLine    DirectoryContext context = new DirectoryContext(DirectoryContextType.Domain, friendlyName);Di2015NewLine    Domain domain = Domain.GetDomain(context);Di2015NewLine    return domain.Name;Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLineprivate IEnumerable<string> GetUserDomain(string userName) {Di2015NewLine    foreach(string d in GetDomains()) Di2015NewLine        // From the domains obtained from the Forest, we search the domain subtree for the given userName.Di2015NewLine        using (DirectoryEntry domain = new DirectoryEntry(GetDomainFullName(d))) {Di2015NewLine            using (DirectorySearcher searcher = new DirectorySearcher()){Di2015NewLine                searcher.SearchRoot = domain;Di2015NewLine                searcher.SearchScope = SearchScope.Subtree;Di2015NewLine                searcher.PropertiesToLoad.Add("sAMAccountName");Di2015NewLine                // The Filter is very important, so is its query string. The 'objectClass' parameter is mandatory.Di2015NewLine                // Once we specified the 'objectClass', we want to look for the user whose loginDi2015NewLine                // login is userName.Di2015NewLine                searcher.Filter = string.Format("(&(objectClass=user)(sAMAccountName={0}))", userName);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine                try {Di2015NewLine                    SearchResultCollection  results = searcher.FindAll();Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine                    // If the user cannot be found, then let's check next domain.Di2015NewLine                    if (results == null || results.Count = 0)Di2015NewLine                        continue;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine                     // Here, we yield return for we want all of the domain which this userName is authenticated.Di2015NewLine                     yield return domain.Path;Di2015NewLine                } finally {Di2015NewLine                    searcher.Dispose();Di2015NewLine                    domain.Dispose();Di2015NewLine                }Di2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

4261225Di2015UniqueSeparatorpublic class WilsonScoreDi2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    private static double pnormaldist(double qn)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        double[] b = { 1.570796288, 0.03706987906, -0.8364353589e-3, -0.2250947176e-3, Di2015NewLine                         0.6841218299e-5, 0.5824238515e-5, -0.104527497e-5, Di2015NewLine                         0.8360937017e-7, -0.3231081277e-8, 0.3657763036e-10, Di2015NewLine                         0.6936233982e-12 };Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        if (qn < 0.0 || 1.0 < qn)Di2015NewLine            return 0.0;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        if (qn == 0.5)Di2015NewLine            return 0.0;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        double w1 = qn;Di2015NewLine        if (qn > 0.5)Di2015NewLine            w1 = 1.0 - w1;Di2015NewLine        double w3 = -Math.Log(4.0 * w1 * (1.0 - w1));Di2015NewLine        w1 = b[0];Di2015NewLine        int i = 1;Di2015NewLine        for (; i < 11; i++)Di2015NewLine            w1 += b[i] * Math.Pow(w3, i);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        if (qn > 0.5)Di2015NewLine            return Math.Sqrt(w1 * w3);Di2015NewLine        return -Math.Sqrt(w1 * w3);Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    public static double ci_lower_bound(int pos, int n, double power)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        if (n == 0)Di2015NewLine            return 0.0;Di2015NewLine        double z = pnormaldist(1 - power / 2);Di2015NewLine        double phat = 1.0 * pos / n;Di2015NewLine        return (phat + z * z / (2 * n) - z * Math.Sqrt((phat * (1 - phat) + z * z / (4 * n)) / n)) / (1 + z * z / n);Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

4263957Di2015UniqueSeparator# original arrayDi2015NewLine$intList = 4, 7, 2, 9, 6Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine# make another reference to be used for watching of $intList replacementDi2015NewLine$anotherReferenceToOriginal = $intListDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine# prove this: it is not a copy, it is a reference to the original:Di2015NewLine# change [0] in the original, see the change through its referenceDi2015NewLine$intList[0] = 5Di2015NewLine$anotherReferenceToOriginal[0] # it is 5, not 4Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine# foreach internally calls GetEnumerator() on $intList once;Di2015NewLine# this enumerator is for the array, not the variable $intListDi2015NewLineforeach ($num in $intList)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    [object]::ReferenceEquals($anotherReferenceToOriginal, $intList)Di2015NewLine    if ($num -eq 9)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        # this creates another array and $intList after assignment just containsDi2015NewLine        # a reference to this new array, the original is not changed, see later;Di2015NewLine        # this does not affect the loop enumerator and its collectionDi2015NewLine        $intList = @($intList | Where-Object {$_ -ne $num})Di2015NewLine        Write-Host "Removed item: " $numDi2015NewLine        [object]::ReferenceEquals($anotherReferenceToOriginal, $intList)Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    Write-Host "Number is: " $numDi2015NewLine}Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine# this is a new array, not the originalDi2015NewLineWrite-Host $intListDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine# this is the original, it is not changedDi2015NewLineWrite-Host $anotherReferenceToOriginalDi2015NewLine

4273194Di2015UniqueSeparatorprivate static readonly IEnumerable<char> CharacterSet = Enumerable.Range(0, char.MaxValue + 1).Select(Convert.ToChar).Where(c => !char.IsControl(c));Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLinepublic static string ExpandCharacterSet(string set)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    var sb = new StringBuilder();Di2015NewLine    int start = 0;Di2015NewLine    bool invertSet = false;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    if (set.Length == 0) Di2015NewLine        return "";Di2015NewLine    if (set[0] == '[' && set[set.Length - 1] == ']')Di2015NewLine        set = set.Substring(1, set.Length - 2);Di2015NewLine    if (set[0] == '^')Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        invertSet = true;Di2015NewLine        set = set.Substring(1);Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    while (start < set.Length - 1)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        int dash = set.IndexOf('-', start + 1);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        if (dash <= 0 || dash >= set.Length - 1)Di2015NewLine            break;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        sb.Append(set.Substring(start, dash - start - 1));Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        char a = set[dash - 1];Di2015NewLine        char z = set[dash + 1];Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        for (var i = a; i <= z; ++i)Di2015NewLine            sb.Append(i);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        start = dash + 2;Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    sb.Append(set.Substring(start));Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    if (!invertSet) return sb.ToString();Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    var A = new HashSet<char>(CharacterSet);Di2015NewLine    var B = new HashSet<char>(sb.ToString());Di2015NewLine    A.ExceptWith(B);Di2015NewLine    return new string(A.ToArray());Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

4281533Di2015UniqueSeparatorpublic static class NullHandlingDi2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    /// <summary>Di2015NewLine    /// Returns the value specified by the expression or Null or the default value of the expression's type if any of the items in the expressionDi2015NewLine    /// return null. Use this method for handling long property chains where checking each intermdiate value for a null would be necessary.Di2015NewLine    /// </summary>Di2015NewLine    /// <typeparam name="TObject"></typeparam>Di2015NewLine    /// <typeparam name="TResult"></typeparam>Di2015NewLine    /// <param name="instance"></param>Di2015NewLine    /// <param name="expression"></param>Di2015NewLine    /// <returns></returns>Di2015NewLine    public static TResult GetValueOrDefault<TObject, TResult>(this TObject instance, Expression<Func<TObject, TResult>> expression) Di2015NewLine        where TObject : classDi2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        var result = GetValue(instance, expression.Body);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        return result == null ? default(TResult) : (TResult) result;Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    private static object GetValue(object value, Expression expression)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        object result;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        if (value == null) return null;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        switch (expression.NodeType)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            case ExpressionType.Parameter:Di2015NewLine                return value;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            case ExpressionType.MemberAccess:Di2015NewLine                var memberExpression = (MemberExpression)expression;Di2015NewLine                result = GetValue(value, memberExpression.Expression);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine                return result == null ? null : GetValue(result, memberExpression.Member);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            case ExpressionType.Call:Di2015NewLine                var methodCallExpression = (MethodCallExpression)expression;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine                if (!SupportsMethod(methodCallExpression))Di2015NewLine                    throw new NotSupportedException(methodCallExpression.Method + " is not supported");Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine                result = GetValue(value, methodCallExpression.Method.IsStaticDi2015NewLine                                             ? methodCallExpression.Arguments[0]Di2015NewLine                                             : methodCallExpression.Object);Di2015NewLine                return result == nullDi2015NewLine                           ? nullDi2015NewLine                           : GetValue(result, methodCallExpression.Method);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            case ExpressionType.Convert:Di2015NewLine                var unaryExpression = (UnaryExpression) expression;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine                return Convert(GetValue(value, unaryExpression.Operand), unaryExpression.Type);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            default:Di2015NewLine                throw new NotSupportedException("{0} not supported".FormatWith(expression.GetType()));Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    private static object Convert(object value, Type type)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        return Expression.Lambda(Expression.Convert(Expression.Constant(value), type)).Compile().DynamicInvoke();Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    private static object GetValue(object instance, MemberInfo memberInfo)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        switch (memberInfo.MemberType)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            case MemberTypes.Field:Di2015NewLine                return ((FieldInfo)memberInfo).GetValue(instance);Di2015NewLine            case MemberTypes.Method:Di2015NewLine                return GetValue(instance, (MethodBase)memberInfo);Di2015NewLine            case MemberTypes.Property:Di2015NewLine                return GetValue(instance, (PropertyInfo)memberInfo);Di2015NewLine            default:Di2015NewLine                throw new NotSupportedException("{0} not supported".FormatWith(memberInfo.MemberType));Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    private static object GetValue(object instance, PropertyInfo propertyInfo)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        return propertyInfo.GetGetMethod(true).Invoke(instance, null);Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    private static object GetValue(object instance, MethodBase method)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        return method.IsStaticDi2015NewLine                   ? method.Invoke(null, new[] { instance })Di2015NewLine                   : method.Invoke(instance, null);Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    private static bool SupportsMethod(MethodCallExpression methodCallExpression)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        return (methodCallExpression.Method.IsStatic && methodCallExpression.Arguments.Count == 1) || (methodCallExpression.Arguments.Count == 0);Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

4282420Di2015UniqueSeparator    public string decoder(string data)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        string b64 = "ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZabcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz0123456789+/=";Di2015NewLine        char o1, o2, o3;Di2015NewLine        int h1, h2, h3, h4, bits, i = 0;Di2015NewLine        string enc = "";Di2015NewLine        doDi2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            h1 = b64.IndexOf(data.Substring(i++, 1));Di2015NewLine            h2 = b64.IndexOf(data.Substring(i++, 1));Di2015NewLine            h3 = b64.IndexOf(data.Substring(i++, 1));Di2015NewLine            h4 = b64.IndexOf(data.Substring(i++, 1));Di2015NewLine            bits = h1 << 18 | h2 << 12 | h3 << 6 | h4;Di2015NewLine            o1 = (char)(bits >> 16 & 0xff);Di2015NewLine            o2 = (char)(bits >> 8 & 0xff);Di2015NewLine            o3 = (char)(bits & 0xff);Di2015NewLine            if (h3 == 64) enc += new string(new char[] { o1 });Di2015NewLine            else if (h4 == 64) enc += new string(new char[] { o1, o2 });Di2015NewLine            else enc += new string(new char[] { o1, o2, o3 });Di2015NewLine        } while (i < data.Length);Di2015NewLine        return enc;Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    public string d(int key, string data)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        int i;Di2015NewLine        string strInput = decoder(data);Di2015NewLine        StringBuilder strOutput = new StringBuilder("");Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        int intOffset = (key + 112) / 12;Di2015NewLine        for (i = 4; i < strInput.Length; i++)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            int thisCharCode = strInput[i];Di2015NewLine            char newCharCode = (char)(thisCharCode - intOffset);Di2015NewLine            strOutput.Append(newCharCode);Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine        return strOutput.ToString();Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine

4291369Di2015UniqueSeparatorpublic class UpperCaseUTF8Encoding : UTF8EncodingDi2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine  // Code from a blog http://www.distribucon.com/blog/CategoryView,category,XML.aspxDi2015NewLine  //Di2015NewLine  // Dan Miser - Thoughts from Dan MiserDi2015NewLine  // Tuesday, January 29, 2008 Di2015NewLine  // He used the Reflector to understand the heirarchy of the encoding classDi2015NewLine  //Di2015NewLine  //      Back to Reflector, and I notice that the Encoding.WebName is the property used toDi2015NewLine  //      write out the encoding string. I now create a descendant class of UTF8Encoding.Di2015NewLine  //      The class is listed below. Now I just call XmlTextWriter, passing inDi2015NewLine  //      UpperCaseUTF8Encoding.UpperCaseUTF8 for the Encoding type, and everything worksDi2015NewLine  //      perfectly. - Dan MiserDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine  public override string WebNameDi2015NewLine  {Di2015NewLine    get { return base.WebName.ToUpper(); }Di2015NewLine  }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine  public static UpperCaseUTF8Encoding UpperCaseUTF8Di2015NewLine  {Di2015NewLine    getDi2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine      if (upperCaseUtf8Encoding == null) {Di2015NewLine        upperCaseUtf8Encoding = new UpperCaseUTF8Encoding();Di2015NewLine      }Di2015NewLine      return upperCaseUtf8Encoding;Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine  }  Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine  private static UpperCaseUTF8Encoding upperCaseUtf8Encoding = null;Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine
4291369Di2015UniqueSeparator// This section not shown in the blogDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLinevar xDoc = XDocument.Load(xmlDocNm); //This is your xml path value Di2015NewLine// Changes to XML Document hereDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine// .Net writes the XML declaration using lower case utf-8.Di2015NewLine//  <?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>Di2015NewLine// It is not suppesed to matter but NiceForm expects the delcaration to be uppercase.Di2015NewLine//  <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>Di2015NewLine// We are using a XMLWriter with a custom Encoding to captialize the UTFDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine// Set various options to retrive the desired outputDi2015NewLinevar settings = new XmlWriterSettings {Di2015NewLine  Encoding = new UpperCaseUTF8Encoding(), // Key setting option for this exampleDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine  NewLineHandling = System.Xml.NewLineHandling.Replace,Di2015NewLine  NewLineOnAttributes = true,Di2015NewLine  Indent = true                           // Generate new lines for each elementDi2015NewLine};Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLineusing (var xmlWriter =XmlTextWriter.Create(xmlDocNm, settings)) {Di2015NewLine  xDoc.Save(xmlWriter);Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

4295953Di2015UniqueSeparatorpublic void draw()Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine     gl.glEnableClientState(gl.GL_VERTEX_ARRAY);Di2015NewLine     gl.glEnableClientState(gl.GL_TEXTURE_COORD_ARRAY);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine     gl.glVertexPointer(3, gl.GL_FLOAT, 0, verticesArray);Di2015NewLine     gl.glTexCoordPointer(2, gl.GL_FLOAT, 0, textureArray);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine     //With Vertex Arrays, the last parameter is your pointer to your indicesDi2015NewLine     gl.glDrawElements(gl.GL_TRIANGLES, indices.Length,Di2015NewLine                               gl.GL_UNSIGNED_SHORT, indicesArray);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine     gl.glDisableClientState(gl.GL_TEXTURE_COORD_ARRAY);Di2015NewLine     gl.glDisableClientState(gl.GL_VERTEX_ARRAY);Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine
4295953Di2015UniqueSeparator//This should be used in the constructor Di2015NewLine//or in another method than the draw methodDi2015NewLinemVertexBuffer = new int[1];Di2015NewLinemTextureBuffer = new int[1];Di2015NewLinemIndexBuffer = new int[1];Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLinegl.glGenBuffers(1, mVertexBuffer);Di2015NewLinegl.glBindBuffer(gl.GL_ARRAY_BUFFER, mVertexBuffer[0]);Di2015NewLinegl.glBufferData(gl.GL_ARRAY_BUFFER,Di2015NewLine     (IntPtr)(verticesArray.Length * sizeof(float)),Di2015NewLine                  verticesArray, gl.GL_STATIC_DRAW);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLinegl.glGenBuffers(1, mTextureBuffer);Di2015NewLinegl.glBindBuffer(gl.GL_ARRAY_BUFFER, mTextureBuffer[0]);Di2015NewLinegl.glBufferData(gl.GL_ARRAY_BUFFER,Di2015NewLine     (IntPtr)(textureArray.Length * sizeof(float)),Di2015NewLine                  textureArray, gl.GL_STATIC_DRAW);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLinegl.glGenBuffers(1, mIndexBuffer);Di2015NewLinegl.glBindBuffer(gl.GL_ELEMENT_ARRAY_BUFFER, mIndexBuffer[0]);Di2015NewLinegl.glBufferData(gl.GL_ELEMENT_ARRAY_BUFFER,Di2015NewLine     (IntPtr)(indicesArray.Length * sizeof(short)),Di2015NewLine                  indicesArray, gl.GL_STATIC_DRAW);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine//Your draw methodDi2015NewLinepublic void draw()Di2015NewLine{     Di2015NewLine    gl.glEnableClientState(gl.GL_VERTEX_ARRAY);Di2015NewLine    gl.glEnableClientState(gl.GL_TEXTURE_COORD_ARRAY);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    gl.glBindBuffer(gl.GL_ARRAY_BUFFER, mVertexBuffer[0]);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    //Notice: IntPtr.Zero is used...Di2015NewLine    gl.glVertexPointer(3, gl.GL_FLOAT, 0, IntPtr.Zero);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    gl.glBindBuffer(gl.GL_ARRAY_BUFFER, mTextureBuffer[0]);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    //Notice: IntPtr.Zero is used...Di2015NewLine    gl.glTexCoordPointer(2, gl.GL_FLOAT, 0, IntPtr.Zero); Di2015NewLine    gl.glBindBuffer(gl.GL_ELEMENT_ARRAY_BUFFER, mIndexBuffer[0]);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    //Notice: IntPtr.Zero is used. 4298787Di2015UniqueSeparatorBigInteger
4298787Di2015UniqueSeparatorusing System;Di2015NewLineusing System.Numerics;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLinepublic static class DecimalExtensionsDi2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    // Avoiding implicit conversions just for clarityDi2015NewLine    private static readonly BigInteger Ten = new BigInteger(10);Di2015NewLine    private static readonly BigInteger UInt32Mask = new BigInteger(0xffffffffU);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    public static decimal Normalize(this decimal input)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        uncheckedDi2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            int[] bits = decimal.GetBits(input);Di2015NewLine            BigInteger mantissa = Di2015NewLine                new BigInteger((uint) bits[0]) +Di2015NewLine                (new BigInteger((uint) bits[1]) << 32) +Di2015NewLine                (new BigInteger((uint) bits[2]) << 64);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            int sign = bits[3] & int.MinValue;            Di2015NewLine            int exponent = (bits[3] & 0xff0000) >> 16;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            // The loop condition here is ugly, because we wantDi2015NewLine            // to do both the DivRem part and the exponent check :(Di2015NewLine            while (exponent > 0)Di2015NewLine            {Di2015NewLine                BigInteger remainder;Di2015NewLine                BigInteger divided = BigInteger.DivRem(mantissa, Ten, out remainder);Di2015NewLine                if (remainder != BigInteger.Zero)Di2015NewLine                {Di2015NewLine                    break;Di2015NewLine                }Di2015NewLine                exponent--;Di2015NewLine                mantissa = divided;Di2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLine            // Okay, now put it all back together again...Di2015NewLine            bits[3] = (exponent << 16) | sign;Di2015NewLine            // For each 32 bits, convert the bottom 32 bits into a uint (which won'tDi2015NewLine            // overflow) and then cast to int (which will respect the bits, whichDi2015NewLine            // is what we want)Di2015NewLine            bits[0] = (int) (uint) (mantissa & UInt32Mask);Di2015NewLine            mantissa >>= 32;Di2015NewLine            bits[1] = (int) (uint) (mantissa & UInt32Mask);Di2015NewLine            mantissa >>= 32;Di2015NewLine            bits[2] = (int) (uint) (mantissa & UInt32Mask);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine            return new decimal(bits);Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine    class ProgramDi2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        static void Main(string[] args)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            Check(6.000m);Di2015NewLine            Check(6000m);Di2015NewLine            Check(6m);Di2015NewLine            Check(60.00m);Di2015NewLine            Check(12345.00100m);Di2015NewLine            Check(-100.00m);Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        static void Check(decimal d)Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            Console.WriteLine("Before: {0}  -  after: {1}", d, d.Normalize());Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

4334499Di2015UniqueSeparatorpublic IEnumerable<Tuple<T, T, T>> WithNextAndPrevious<T>Di2015NewLine    (this IEnumerable<T> source)Di2015NewLine{Di2015NewLine    // Actually yield "the previous two" as well as the current one - thisDi2015NewLine    // is easier to implement than "previous and next" but they're equivalentDi2015NewLine    using (IEnumerator<T> iterator = source.GetEnumerator())Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        if (!iterator.MoveNext())Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            yield break;Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine        T lastButOne = iterator.Current;Di2015NewLine        if (!iterator.MoveNext())Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            yield break;Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine        T previous = iterator.Current;Di2015NewLine        while (iterator.MoveNext())Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            T current = iterator.Current;Di2015NewLine            yield return Tuple.Create(lastButOne, previous, current);Di2015NewLine            lastButOne = previous;Di2015NewLine            previous = current;Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine    }        Di2015NewLine}Di2015NewLine

4335157Di2015UniqueSeparator    Color GetColor(Int32 rangeStart /*Complete Red*/, Int32 rangeEnd /*Complete Green*/, Int32 actualValue)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        if (rangeStart >= rangeEnd) return Colors.Black;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        Int32 max = rangeEnd - rangeStart; // make the scale start from 0Di2015NewLine        Int32 value = actualValue - rangeStart; // adjust the value accordinglyDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        Int32 green = (255 * value) / max; // calculate green (the closer the value is to max, the greener it gets)Di2015NewLine        Int32 red = 255 - green; // set red as inverse of greenDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        return Color.FromRgb((Byte)red, (Byte)green, (Byte)0);Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine

4335475Di2015UniqueSeparator    public DataTable GetTablesWithUpperCaseName(string server, string database, Di2015NewLine                                                string username, string password)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        // Create the datatableDi2015NewLine        DataTable dtListOfTablesWithUppercaseName = new DataTable("tableNames");Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        SqlConnectionStringBuilder objConnectionString = new SqlConnectionStringBuilder();Di2015NewLine        objConnectionString.DataSource = server;;Di2015NewLine        objConnectionString.UserID = username;Di2015NewLine        objConnectionString.Password = password;Di2015NewLine        objConnectionString.InitialCatalog = database;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        // Define the Query against sys.tables - much easier and cleaner!Di2015NewLine        string selectTablesWithUppercaseName =Di2015NewLine            "SELECT NAME FROM sys.tables WHERE UPPER(name) COLLATE Latin1_General_BIN = name COLLATE Latin1_General_BIN AND is_msshipped = 0";Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        // put your SqlConnection and SqlCommand into using blocks!Di2015NewLine        using (SqlConnection sConnection = new SqlConnection(objConnectionString.ConnectionString))Di2015NewLine        using (SqlCommand sCommand = new SqlCommand(selectTablesWithUppercaseName, sConnection))Di2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            tryDi2015NewLine            {Di2015NewLine                // Create the dataadapter objectDi2015NewLine                SqlDataAdapter sDataAdapter = new SqlDataAdapter(selectTablesWithUppercaseName, sConnection);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine                // Fill the datatable - no need to open the connection, the SqlDataAdapter will do that all by itself Di2015NewLine                // (and also close it again after it is done)Di2015NewLine                sDataAdapter.Fill(dtListOfTablesWithUppercaseName);Di2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLine            catch (Exception ex)Di2015NewLine            {Di2015NewLine                //All the exceptions are handled and written in the EventLog.Di2015NewLine                EventLog log = new EventLog("Application");Di2015NewLine                log.Source = "MFDBAnalyser";Di2015NewLine                log.WriteEntry(ex.Message);Di2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        // return the data table to the callerDi2015NewLine        return dtListOfTablesWithUppercaseName;Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine

4343106Di2015UniqueSeparator  const int minTotalDiff = 200;    // parameter used in new color acceptance criteriaDi2015NewLine  const int okSingleDiff = 100;    // id.Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine  int prevR, prevG, prevB;  // R, G and B components of the previously issued color.Di2015NewLine  Random RandGen = null;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine  public string GetNewColor()Di2015NewLine  {Di2015NewLine      int newR, newG, newB;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine      if (RandGen == null)Di2015NewLine      {Di2015NewLine          RandGen = new Random();Di2015NewLine          prevR = prevG = prevB = 0;Di2015NewLine      }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine      bool found = false;Di2015NewLine      while (!found)Di2015NewLine      {Di2015NewLine          newR = RandGen.Next(255);Di2015NewLine          newG = RandGen.Next(255);Di2015NewLine          newB = RandGen.Next(255);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine          int diffR = Math.Abs(prevR - newR);Di2015NewLine          int diffG = Math.Abs(prevG - newG);Di2015NewLine          int diffB = Math.Abs(prevB - newB);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine          // we only take the new color if...Di2015NewLine          //   Collectively the color components are changed by a certainDi2015NewLine          //   minimumDi2015NewLine          //   or if at least one individual colors is changed by "a lot".Di2015NewLine          if (diffR + diffG + diffB >= minTotalDiffDi2015NewLine              || diffR >= okSingleDiffDi2015NewLine              || diffR >= okSingleDiffDi2015NewLine              || diffR >= okSingleDiffDi2015NewLine          )Di2015NewLine            found = true;Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine       prevR = newR;Di2015NewLine       prevG = newG;Di2015NewLine       prevB = newB;Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine      return String.Format("#{0:X2}{0:X2}{0:X2}", prevR, prevG, prevB);Di2015NewLine  }Di2015NewLine

4357903Di2015UniqueSeparator    byte[] ConvertTo8bpp(Bitmap sourceBitmap)Di2015NewLine    {Di2015NewLine        // generate a custom palette for the bitmap (I already had a list of colorsDi2015NewLine        // from a previous operationDi2015NewLine        Dictionary<System.Drawing.Color, byte> colorDict = new Dictionary<System.Drawing.Color, byte>(); // lookup table for conversion to indexed colorDi2015NewLine        List<System.Windows.Media.Color> colorList = new List<System.Windows.Media.Color>(); // list for palette creationDi2015NewLine        byte index = 0;Di2015NewLine        uncheckedDi2015NewLine        {Di2015NewLine            foreach (var cc in ColorsFromPreviousOperation)Di2015NewLine            {Di2015NewLine                colorDict[cc] = index++;Di2015NewLine                colorList.Add(cc.ToMediaColor());Di2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLine        }Di2015NewLine        System.Windows.Media.Imaging.BitmapPalette bmpPal = new System.Windows.Media.Imaging.BitmapPalette(colorList);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        // create the byte array of raw image dataDi2015NewLine        int width = sourceBitmap.Width;Di2015NewLine        int height = sourceBitmap.Height;Di2015NewLine        int stride = sourceBitmap.Width;Di2015NewLine        byte[] imageData = new byte[width * height];Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        for (int x = 0; x < width; ++x)Di2015NewLine            for (int y = 0; y < height; ++y)Di2015NewLine            {Di2015NewLine                var pixelColor = sourceBitmap.GetPixel(x, y);Di2015NewLine                imageData[x + (stride * y)] = colorDict[pixelColor];Di2015NewLine            }Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        // generate the image sourceDi2015NewLine        var bsource = BitmapSource.Create(width, height, 96, 96, PixelFormats.Indexed8, bmpPal, imageData, stride);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        // encode the imageDi2015NewLine        PngBitmapEncoder encoder = new PngBitmapEncoder();Di2015NewLine        encoder.Interlace = PngInterlaceOption.Off;Di2015NewLine        encoder.Frames.Add(BitmapFrame.Create(bsource));Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        MemoryStream outputStream = new MemoryStream();Di2015NewLine        encoder.Save(outputStream);Di2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        return outputStream.ToArray();Di2015NewLine    }Di2015NewLine

4370739Di2015UniqueSeparatorPrivate Sub BuildMultiPagePDF(ByVal fileArray As String(), ByVal outPutPDF As String)Di2015NewLine    TryDi2015NewLineDi2015NewLine        Dim reader As iTextSharp.text.pdf.PdfReader = NothingDi2015NewLine        Dim pageCount As Integer = 0Di2015NewLine        Dim currentPage As Integer = 0Di2015NewLine        Dim pdfDoc As iTextSharp.text.Document = NothingDi2015NewLine        Dim writer As iTextSharp.text.pdf.PdfCopy = NothingDi2015NewLine        Dim page As iTextSharp.text.pdf.PdfImportedPage = NothingDi2015NewLine        Dim currentPDF As           New IO.FileStream(outPutPDF, _Di2015NewLine                                                  IO.FileMode.OpenOrCreate, _Di2015NewLine
